---
import BaseLayout from '../../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Install Claude Code First, Then Connect VS Code to Get Started"
  description="A step-by-step guide to installing, launching, and signing in to Claude Code on Mac and Windows, with fixes for the most common beginner issues."
  lang="en"
>
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container cc-install">
      <a class="back-link" href="/">&larr; Back to Home</a>

      <header class="detail-header">
        <h1 class="detail-title">Install Claude Code First, Then Connect VS Code to Get Started</h1>
        <p class="detail-subtitle">
          From what to prepare beforehand, to installing on Mac or Windows, signing in to your
          account, and fixing the most common hiccups — this guide walks you through getting
          Claude Code up and running, step by step.
        </p>
      </header>

      <!-- Overview Diagram -->
      <h2 class="detail-heading">Quick Overview</h2>
      <p class="detail-paragraph">
        The diagram below summarizes the five main stages of the whole process, from preparing
        your environment to starting your first project — so you can get a sense of the big
        picture before diving in.
      </p>
      <figure class="overview-figure">
        <img
          src="/learning/claude-code/install-en.png"
          alt="Overview diagram of the Claude Code installation and setup flow"
          loading="lazy"
        />
      </figure>

      <!-- Section: Prerequisites -->
      <h2 class="detail-heading">Before You Start: Two Things to Prepare</h2>
      <p class="detail-paragraph">
        Before installing Claude Code, please make sure you have the following two things ready:
      </p>

      <div class="prep-grid">
        <div class="prep-card">
          <p class="prep-index">01</p>
          <h3 class="prep-title">A project folder</h3>
          <p class="prep-desc">
            Create an empty folder on your computer. This will be the workspace where the AI
            helps you write code and manage files. It is a good idea to put it somewhere easy to
            find, such as your Desktop or Documents folder.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="prep-card">
          <p class="prep-index">02</p>
          <h3 class="prep-title">A paid account</h3>
          <p class="prep-desc">
            Claude Code currently requires a
            <strong>Claude Pro</strong> subscription (US$20 per month) or the more advanced
            <strong>Max</strong> plan. Please sign up and complete the payment on the Claude
            website first.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Section: Mac Install -->
      <h2 class="detail-heading">Installing on Mac</h2>
      <p class="detail-paragraph">
        <span class="platform-badge platform-badge--mac">macOS</span>
        Installation on a Mac is very simple — all you need is the built-in Terminal app.
      </p>

      <ol class="step-list">
        <li class="step-item">
          <span class="step-num">1</span>
          <div class="step-body">
            <h3 class="step-title">Open the Terminal</h3>
            <p class="step-desc">
              Press <kbd>⌘</kbd> + <kbd>Space</kbd> to bring up Spotlight, type
              "Terminal", and press Enter. A window with a black-on-white (or white-on-black)
              background will appear.
            </p>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li class="step-item">
          <span class="step-num">2</span>
          <div class="step-body">
            <h3 class="step-title">Paste the install command</h3>
            <p class="step-desc">
              Copy the command below and paste it into the Terminal window you just opened:
            </p>
            <pre class="code-block"><code>curl -fsSL https://claude.ai/install.sh | bash</code></pre>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li class="step-item">
          <span class="step-num">3</span>
          <div class="step-body">
            <h3 class="step-title">Press Enter</h3>
            <p class="step-desc">
              Your computer will install Claude Code automatically — just wait for it to finish.
              If any prompt shows up along the way, simply follow the on-screen instructions.
            </p>
          </div>
        </li>
      </ol>

      <!-- Section: Windows Install -->
      <h2 class="detail-heading">Installing on Windows</h2>
      <p class="detail-paragraph">
        <span class="platform-badge platform-badge--win">Windows</span>
        Windows installation takes one extra step, so please follow the order carefully.
      </p>

      <ol class="step-list">
        <li class="step-item">
          <span class="step-num">1</span>
          <div class="step-body">
            <h3 class="step-title">Install "Git" first (very important!)</h3>
            <p class="step-desc">
              On Windows, Claude Code requires Git to be installed before it can run.
              Search Google for "<strong>Git for Windows</strong>" and download the installer.
              During installation, you can simply keep clicking "Next" all the way through.
            </p>
            <p class="step-note">
              Quick tip: if you see an option called "<strong>Add to PATH</strong>" during
              installation, make sure it is checked. After the installation finishes, please
              close all windows first.
            </p>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li class="step-item">
          <span class="step-num">2</span>
          <div class="step-body">
            <h3 class="step-title">Open "PowerShell"</h3>
            <p class="step-desc">
              Click the Windows Start button in the lower-left corner of the screen, type
              "PowerShell", and open it. A command window with a blue or black background will
              appear.
            </p>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li class="step-item">
          <span class="step-num">3</span>
          <div class="step-body">
            <h3 class="step-title">Paste the install command</h3>
            <p class="step-desc">
              Copy the command below, paste it into the PowerShell window, and press Enter:
            </p>
            <pre class="code-block"><code>curl -fsSL https://claude.ai/install.sh | bash</code></pre>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li class="step-item">
          <span class="step-num">4</span>
          <div class="step-body">
            <h3 class="step-title">Close and "reopen" PowerShell</h3>
            <p class="step-desc">
              After the installer finishes, be sure to close the PowerShell window and open a
              brand new one. This step is needed so your computer can recognize the newly
              installed tool.
            </p>
          </div>
        </li>
      </ol>

      <!-- Section: Launch & Login -->
      <h2 class="detail-heading">Launching and Signing In</h2>
      <p class="detail-paragraph">
        Once the installation steps above are done, you are ready to launch Claude Code for the
        first time.
      </p>

      <ol class="step-list">
        <li class="step-item">
          <span class="step-num">1</span>
          <div class="step-body">
            <h3 class="step-title">Call the AI assistant</h3>
            <p class="step-desc">
              In the Terminal (or PowerShell) window, type the following command and press Enter:
            </p>
            <pre class="code-block"><code>claude</code></pre>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li class="step-item">
          <span class="step-num">2</span>
          <div class="step-body">
            <h3 class="step-title">Authorize in the browser</h3>
            <p class="step-desc">
              The first time you launch it, a browser window will open automatically. Check that
              the Claude account shown is yours, then click the
              "<strong>Approve</strong>" button.
            </p>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li class="step-item">
          <span class="step-num">3</span>
          <div class="step-body">
            <h3 class="step-title">All done!</h3>
            <p class="step-desc">
              Close the browser page and go back to the command window. You will see that Claude
              Code has started and is greeting you. It may ask whether you want to trust this
              folder — choose yes, and you can start chatting.
            </p>
          </div>
        </li>
      </ol>

      <!-- Section: Troubleshooting -->
      <h2 class="detail-heading">Beginner Troubleshooting</h2>
      <p class="detail-paragraph">
        Small hiccups sometimes come up during installation, especially on Windows. Here are the
        most common issues and how to fix them:
      </p>

      <div class="faq-card">
        <div class="faq-tag">Common Windows pitfall</div>
        <h3 class="faq-question">
          After typing <code>claude</code>, you see a red error saying "The term 'claude' is not
          recognized as the name of a cmdlet…"
        </h3>
        <p class="faq-desc">
          This means your computer cannot "find" the file you just installed. Try the following
          steps:
        </p>
        <ol class="faq-steps">
          <li>
            <strong>Close PowerShell and reopen it.</strong>
            The most common cause is simply forgetting to reopen PowerShell after installing.
            Try this first.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>If reopening does not help, add the environment variable manually.</strong>
            In PowerShell, type the following command and press Enter:
            <pre class="code-block code-block--small"><code>$env:PATH += ";$env:USERPROFILE\.local\bin"</code></pre>
            Then <strong>once again</strong> close PowerShell and open a new window, and type
            <code>claude</code>. In most cases, this will solve the issue cleanly.
          </li>
        </ol>
      </div>

      <!-- Section: Optional VS Code GUI -->
      <h2 class="detail-heading">
        <span class="optional-badge">Optional</span>
        Give Claude Code a Friendly Graphical Interface
      </h2>
      <p class="detail-paragraph">
        Once you have finished the terminal installation above, your computer already has the
        "smart brain" of Claude Code. The steps below show you how to install a free program
        called <strong>Visual Studio Code</strong> (VS Code for short), which gives that brain
        a nice, easy-to-use "control panel". With it, you no longer need to stare at a
        black-and-white terminal window — you can click buttons with your mouse to approve
        tasks and clearly see which files the AI has changed.
      </p>

      <ol class="step-list">
        <li class="step-item">
          <span class="step-num">1</span>
          <div class="step-body">
            <h3 class="step-title">Download and install VS Code</h3>
            <p class="step-desc">Set up your very own digital workbench.</p>
            <ol class="substep-list">
              <li>
                Open your browser and search for
                "<strong>VS Code</strong>" (or Visual Studio Code).
              </li>
              <li>
                On the official website, the page automatically detects whether you are on a
                Mac or a Windows PC — click the "<strong>Download</strong>" button.
              </li>
              <li>
                Once the download is complete, run the installer. Installation is as simple as
                any other program — just keep clicking "Next" until it finishes, then open
                VS Code.
              </li>
            </ol>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li class="step-item">
          <span class="step-num">2</span>
          <div class="step-body">
            <h3 class="step-title">Prepare a dedicated "work room" (folder)</h3>
            <p class="step-desc">
              The AI assistant needs a clear scope to work in — that scope is a folder.
            </p>
            <ol class="substep-list">
              <li>
                On your desktop, right-click and
                <strong>create a new empty folder</strong>. This will be your future project
                folder.
              </li>
              <li>Open the VS Code program you just installed.</li>
              <li>
                Drag the empty folder you just created directly into the VS Code window, or
                choose "<strong>Open Folder</strong>" from the top-left menu to open it.
              </li>
            </ol>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li class="step-item">
          <span class="step-num">3</span>
          <div class="step-body">
            <h3 class="step-title">Install the Claude Code extension in VS Code</h3>
            <p class="step-desc">Now let's add the dedicated Claude panel to VS Code.</p>
            <ol class="substep-list">
              <li>
                Look at the vertical strip of icons on the far left of the VS Code window —
                find and click the one that looks like <strong>four small squares</strong>
                (this is the Extensions view).
              </li>
              <li>
                In the search box at the top, type the keyword
                "<strong>Claude Code</strong>".
              </li>
              <li>
                Find the extension published by <strong>Anthropic</strong> and click the
                "<strong>Install</strong>" button next to it.
              </li>
            </ol>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li class="step-item">
          <span class="step-num">4</span>
          <div class="step-body">
            <h3 class="step-title">Launch the assistant and start using it</h3>
            <p class="step-desc">
              After the extension is installed, a dedicated Claude icon will appear in the
              left sidebar of VS Code.
            </p>
            <ol class="substep-list">
              <li>
                Click the Claude icon to open the graphical chat panel. You can also press
                <kbd>Cmd</kbd>+<kbd>Shift</kbd>+<kbd>P</kbd> (Mac) or
                <kbd>Ctrl</kbd>+<kbd>Shift</kbd>+<kbd>P</kbd> (Windows) and type
                "Claude Code" to open it.
              </li>
              <li>
                Because this is your first time using the interface, you will be guided
                through a browser authorization step. Just follow the on-screen instructions
                and click "<strong>Approve</strong>" in the browser window that pops up to
                complete the setup.
              </li>
              <li>
                Back in VS Code, you will see the familiar chat box. From here on, you can
                describe what you want in plain language and let the AI write code for you.
              </li>
            </ol>
          </div>
        </li>
      </ol>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .cc-install {
    max-width: 52rem;
  }

  .back-link {
    display: inline-block;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-8);
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    color: var(--color-accent);
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  .back-link:hover {
    text-decoration: underline;
  }

  /* Header */
  .detail-header {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-12);
    padding-bottom: var(--space-6);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  .detail-title {
    font-size: var(--text-3xl);
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-heading);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-3);
    line-height: 1.3;
  }

  .detail-subtitle {
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  /* Section headings */
  .detail-heading {
    font-size: var(--text-xl);
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--color-heading);
    margin-top: var(--space-12);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
    padding-bottom: var(--space-2);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  .detail-paragraph {
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    color: var(--color-text);
    line-height: 1.9;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
  }

  .detail-paragraph strong {
    color: var(--color-heading);
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  /* Overview figure */
  .overview-figure {
    margin: var(--space-6) 0 var(--space-8);
    padding: var(--space-4);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: var(--border-radius);
    background-color: var(--color-bg-secondary);
  }

  .overview-figure img {
    display: block;
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
    border-radius: var(--border-radius);
  }

  /* Prep cards */
  .prep-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: var(--space-4);
    margin: var(--space-6) 0 var(--space-8);
  }

  .prep-card {
    padding: var(--space-8);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: var(--border-radius);
    background-color: var(--color-bg-secondary);
    transition: all var(--transition);
  }

  .prep-card:hover {
    border-color: var(--color-accent);
    transform: translateY(-2px);
  }

  .prep-index {
    font-size: var(--text-xs);
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-2);
  }

  .prep-title {
    font-size: var(--text-lg);
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-heading);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-3);
  }

  .prep-desc {
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    color: var(--color-text);
    line-height: 1.8;
  }

  .prep-desc strong {
    color: var(--color-heading);
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  /* Platform badge */
  .platform-badge {
    display: inline-block;
    padding: var(--space-1) var(--space-3);
    margin-right: var(--space-2);
    font-size: var(--text-xs);
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
    border-radius: var(--border-radius);
  }

  .platform-badge--mac {
    background-color: var(--color-tag-bg);
    color: var(--color-tag-text);
  }

  .platform-badge--win {
    background-color: var(--color-tag-bg);
    color: var(--color-tag-text);
  }

  /* Step list (numbered) */
  .step-list {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: var(--space-6) 0 var(--space-8);
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-4);
  }

  .step-item {
    display: flex;
    align-items: flex-start;
    gap: var(--space-6);
    padding: var(--space-8);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: var(--border-radius);
    background-color: var(--color-bg-secondary);
    transition: all var(--transition);
  }

  .step-item:hover {
    border-color: var(--color-accent);
  }

  .step-num {
    flex-shrink: 0;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    width: 2.5rem;
    height: 2.5rem;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background-color: var(--color-accent);
    color: #fff;
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    font-weight: 700;
  }

  .step-body {
    flex: 1;
    min-width: 0;
  }

  .step-title {
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--color-heading);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-2);
  }

  .step-desc {
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    color: var(--color-text);
    line-height: 1.8;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-3);
  }

  .step-desc:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .step-desc strong {
    color: var(--color-heading);
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .step-note {
    margin-top: var(--space-3);
    padding: var(--space-3) var(--space-4);
    font-size: var(--text-xs);
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.8;
    background-color: var(--color-bg);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--color-accent);
    border-radius: var(--border-radius);
  }

  .step-note strong {
    color: var(--color-heading);
  }

  /* Code block */
  .code-block {
    display: block;
    margin: var(--space-3) 0 0;
    padding: var(--space-4);
    background-color: #0f172a;
    color: #e2e8f0;
    font-family: ui-monospace, SFMono-Regular, Menlo, Consolas, monospace;
    font-size: var(--text-xs);
    line-height: 1.7;
    border-radius: var(--border-radius);
    overflow-x: auto;
    white-space: pre;
  }

  .code-block code {
    font-family: inherit;
    color: inherit;
    background: none;
    padding: 0;
  }

  .code-block--small {
    font-size: var(--text-xs);
  }

  /* Keyboard key */
  kbd {
    display: inline-block;
    padding: 0 var(--space-2);
    font-family: ui-monospace, SFMono-Regular, Menlo, Consolas, monospace;
    font-size: var(--text-xs);
    color: var(--color-text);
    background-color: var(--color-bg);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-bottom-width: 2px;
    border-radius: var(--border-radius);
    vertical-align: middle;
  }

  /* Inline code */
  :global(.faq-card) code,
  :global(.step-desc) code,
  :global(.faq-question) code {
    padding: 0.1em 0.4em;
    font-family: ui-monospace, SFMono-Regular, Menlo, Consolas, monospace;
    font-size: 0.9em;
    background-color: var(--color-tag-bg);
    color: var(--color-tag-text);
    border-radius: var(--border-radius);
  }

  /* FAQ / troubleshooting card */
  .faq-card {
    margin: var(--space-6) 0 var(--space-4);
    padding: var(--space-8);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-accent);
    border-radius: var(--border-radius);
    background-color: var(--color-tag-bg);
  }

  .faq-tag {
    display: inline-block;
    padding: var(--space-1) var(--space-3);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-3);
    background-color: var(--color-accent);
    color: #fff;
    font-size: var(--text-xs);
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
    border-radius: var(--border-radius);
  }

  .faq-question {
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--color-heading);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-3);
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .faq-desc {
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    color: var(--color-text);
    line-height: 1.8;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
  }

  .faq-steps {
    padding-left: var(--space-6);
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-4);
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    color: var(--color-text);
    line-height: 1.8;
  }

  .faq-steps strong {
    color: var(--color-heading);
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  /* Optional badge in heading */
  .optional-badge {
    display: inline-block;
    padding: var(--space-1) var(--space-3);
    margin-right: var(--space-2);
    font-size: var(--text-xs);
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
    background-color: var(--color-accent);
    color: #fff;
    border-radius: var(--border-radius);
    vertical-align: middle;
  }

  /* Sub-steps (a, b, c) inside a step */
  .substep-list {
    list-style: lower-alpha;
    margin: var(--space-3) 0 0;
    padding-left: var(--space-6);
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    color: var(--color-text);
    line-height: 1.8;
  }

  .substep-list li {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-2);
    padding-left: var(--space-1);
  }

  .substep-list li:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .substep-list strong {
    color: var(--color-heading);
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  /* Mobile */
  @media (max-width: 720px) {
    .prep-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .step-item {
      gap: var(--space-4);
      padding: var(--space-6);
    }

    .step-num {
      width: 2rem;
      height: 2rem;
      font-size: var(--text-sm);
    }

    .faq-card {
      padding: var(--space-6);
    }
  }
</style>
